  <span id="freeText7361268444973427866" style="display:none">The antics of 24 year-old Glaswegian James Herriot, getting used to the ropes as a veterinary assistant in 1930s Yorkshire.<br />You really get a glimpse at the Author’s own life, humour &amp; the beautiful dales that so many of us have come to love. 🌄<br />The characters of Skeldale house, along with the eccentric locals - (not forgetting Tricki Woo, the over-indulged Pekingese), will have you really guffawing from start to finish.<br />Only the four stars for me because I’m a but squeamish on the medical procedure front. Which probably isn’t great to read just before you’re about to have your tea... 🤢<br /><br />Overall an enjoyable read though &amp; I look forward to continuing with the series.</span>
