        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3282343235" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2652077579257165026">A well loved and greatly read series. <br/><br/>James Herriot is starting out as a young veterinary assistant in Yorkshire. An interesting, funny, and occasionally warm book, though not for the squeamish. <br/><br/>I ended up watching the series on TV first which I don&apos;t usually do (in case you&apos;re wondering the first three seasons are great and then the rest I wouldn&apos;t bother with). I will give the TV series props because it is dead on to what Herriot wrote. The characters, the plots, the places.<br/><br/></span>
  <span id="freeText2652077579257165026" style="display:none">A well loved and greatly read series. <br /><br />James Herriot is starting out as a young veterinary assistant in Yorkshire. An interesting, funny, and occasionally warm book, though not for the squeamish. <br /><br />I ended up watching the series on TV first which I don't usually do (in case you're wondering the first three seasons are great and then the rest I wouldn't bother with). I will give the TV series props because it is dead on to what Herriot wrote. The characters, the plots, the places.<br /><br /></span>
